<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall brown. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18D</figureCitation>
) brown, with light brown vittae, expansions testaceous, mildly translucent anteriorly. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18A</figureCitation>
) light brown, without any pale-yellow longitudinal stripe. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18B</figureCitation>
) brown, except for trochanters, which are light brown. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18F</figureCitation>
) entirely translucent. Pygidium entirely dark brown or with paired translucent, elongate spots a 1/3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as pygidium.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 18" startId="F18">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Figure 18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys minima" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov. A</emphasis>
, Male habitus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">B</emphasis>
, Male habitus, ventral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C</emphasis>
, Male antenna, lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">D</emphasis>
, Male pronotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">E</emphasis>
, Male terminal segments, ventral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">F</emphasis>
, Pygidium, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">G</emphasis>
, Syntergite, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">H</emphasis>
, Sternum IX, Ventral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">I</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">J</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">K</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18D</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 5.4-6.3 mm (aver. 5.85 mm); Pronotal length = 1.0-1.3 mm (aver. 1.15 mm); Pronotal width = 1.7-2.0 mm (aver. 1.85 mm); Elytral length = 4.7-5.0 mm (aver. 4.85 mm); Elytral width = 1.2-1.4 mm (aver. 1.3 mm). Antennomere III with lamella about 2.x longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI and VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18B, E</figureCitation>
) with translucent spots about 1/2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long and 1/6
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as sterna, lanterns rudimentary. Sterna VI and VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18B, E</figureCitation>
) with minute, central translucent round spots that look like rudimentary lanterns. Sternum VIII with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium with sides rounded, posterior corners weakly developed, posterior margin rounded to almost straight. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18G, H</figureCitation>
) boomerang-shaped (with anterior margin strongly curved). Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18I-K</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate curved almost straight in lateral view, with sides straight and acuminate at apical half. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) rudimentary. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
